Storyline:

Captain Kirk replies to an urgent message from Commodore Enright, which only
tells him to report to the nearest space station. Once there, most of the crew is
removed - held in a security area, leaving only a minimal skeleton crew on-board.
Commodore Bob Wesley arrives, and informs Kirk he's to be the 'fox in the hunt'
of simulated war games to be played. To put the so far only-rumoured-to-exist
M-5 Multitronic unit - through its paces. The M-5 computer is the latest invention
of the brilliant Dr. Richard Daystrom, creator of the Duotronic computer systems,
which run the Enterprise. Daystrom is confidant his unit can not only take control
of the starship, but do a better job than humans can. At first, the Enterprise 
under M-5's control easily defeats two other starships, but, begins to act 
independently of its human masters, Daystrom has no interest in disconnecting the 
M-5 and treats it more like an errant child than a machine. For Kirk and the few 
crew members still aboard, it becomes a matter of life and death when Starfleet 
Command orders the Enterprise destroyed.
